      "body": "> Isn't depends explicitly supported for building on older systems lacking the required dependency versions? (Not just for cross-compiking)\r\n\r\nCould you clarify how that relates to this PR?\r\n\r\nFor context, `depends/hosts/mingw32.mk` is strictly for cross-compiling. While `depends/hosts/darwin.mk` handles both cross-compiling and native static builds, using GNU Make provided by Homebrew is [documented](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/depends/README.md#macos) for the that use case.",
